<body>

	<div class="container">
		<div class="row">
			
			<div class="col-sm-5">
				<div class="iphone white pull" id="dash-demo">
					<div class="frame" id="screenshot-frame">					
						<img src="/worldclock/main852.png" alt="Screenshot of World Clock app">
						<img src="/worldclock/widget852.png" alt="Screenshot of World Clock Today widget" id="widget">
					</div>
				</div>
			</div>
			
			<div class="col-sm-7">
			
				<h1>World Clock</h1>
				<p class="lead">Check the time, anytime.</p>
			
				<p>Need to know if your colleagues in London have gone home for the night? With the World Clock widget, you don&rsquo;t need to open an app or do math in your head &mdash; just pull down Notification Center.</p>
				<p>Add the time zones you want to track. Select the analog or digital clocks. Then check the World Clock widget when you need to know the time.</p>
				
				<a href="https://itunes.apple.com/us/app/world-clock-today-widget/id956377119"><img src="/worldclock/Download_on_the_App_Store_Badge_US-UK_135x40.svg" alt="Cheatsheet in the App Store" class="pad"></a>
				
				<p class="small">
					Made by Adam in California &#8729; 
					<a href="/worldclock/worldclock-press-kit.zip">Press Kit</a> &#8729; 
					<a href="mailto:worldclock@overdesigned.net">Contact</a>
				</p>

			</div>
			

		</div> <!-- /row -->
	</div><!-- /container -->

	<script charset="utf-8">
		document.getElementById("screenshot-frame").addEventListener("click", toggleAnimation);
		function toggleAnimation() {
		    document.getElementById("widget").classList.toggle("paused");
		}
	</script>
</body>
